## Phase 1 ‚Äî Fetch & triage

```bash
gh pr view <N> --json number,title,headRefName,baseRefName,url

gh api graphql -f query='
query { repository(owner:"amo-tech-ai", name:"lumina-studio") {
  pullRequest(number:<N>) {
    reviewThreads(first:100) {
      nodes { id isResolved path line
        comments(first:1) { nodes { databaseId body author { login } } }
      }
    }
  }
}}'

gh api repos/amo-tech-ai/lumina-studio/pulls/<N>/comments \
  --jq '.[] | {id,path,line,user:.user.login,body}'
```

**Bucket every unresolved thread:**

| Bucket | Action |
|--------|--------|
| **Fix** | Valid, in scope, not in HEAD |
| **Already fixed** | Verify at current line on PR branch (+ MCP if DB claim) |
| **Out of scope** | Reply + follow-up Linear title; **do not resolve** |
| **Dismiss** | Wrong assumption ‚Äî reply with skill/MCP/tsc evidence, then resolve |

Show triage table before coding.

